Books at exactly 16:  6 of 21 (28.6%)
Books >=16:          16 of 21 (76.2%)
Books <16:            5 of 21 (23.8%) — challenges, logic, modules, systems, (values ok)
Books missing MANIFEST: 6 of 21 (composition, introspection, modules, scheme, slat, values)

CRITICAL:
- book-of-modules is COMPLETELY EMPTY. This is the successor to book-of-extensions
  under the modules-not-extensions terminology lock. It ships in scheme-books/
  with zero content. The old book-of-extensions material is in
  training-data/wave-1-book-of-extensions-2026-07-16.jsonl (390 corpus rows) but
  the CANONICAL book replacement was never authored. Motoi will train on the OLD
  wording and have NO book to open when a user runs (book/read :book 'modules).
- book-of-motion has 23 chapters — needs merge or promote to appendices per
  '16-chapter invariant + overflow to appendices' doctrine.

VERDICT: 16 of 21 books meet >=16, one is empty, one is overlong. Ship-safe
for exploration; 1.0 needs (a) book-of-modules populated, (b) motion overflow,
(c) below-invariant books extended or annotated.
"

