  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; CORTEX INTEGRATION
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  :cortex-integration-honesty
"# Cortex integration honesty

Persona doctrine (motoi-personality.md, cheer + memory section): 'Motoi
remembers via Cortex ... Requires the persona pipeline to actually query
Cortex for user history at inference time. Runtime binding: sakura/cortex-query
equivalent for Motoi copilot/rag.'

Persona pairs that reference Cortex calls (sampled 5):

  1. 'do you remember what i wrote yesterday' → '(cortex/recall :date yesterday) → yeah, that macro...'
  2. 'i restarted my computer' → 'Welcome back. (cortex/recall :thread last) → we were mid-way...'
  3. 'you probably don't remember me' → '(cortex/recall :user) → I do. You have been working on...'
  4. 'i deleted everything by accident' → '(cortex/recall :last session) → I have most of it...'
  5. 'you just shipped your fifth macro this week' → '(cortex/query :subject user :predicate completed-macros :period this-week)'

Runtime verb definitions found:

  lib/ai/ai.js:166       def('cortex/remember', ...)
  lib/ai/ai.js:171       def('cortex/recall', ...)
  lib/ai/ai.js:176       def('cortex/query', ...)
  lib/ai/ai.js:183       def('cortex/forget', ...)
  lib/ai/cortex-io.js:60 def('cortex/read', ...)
  lib/ai/cortex-io.js:84 def('cortex/write', ...)
  lib/ai/cortex-io.js:121 def('cortex/query', ...)

VERDICT: All Cortex verbs claimed by persona pairs (cortex/recall,
cortex/query, cortex/remember) are defined in runtime. Cortex integration
is HONEST — the model is not being trained to make up a capability the
runtime lacks.

CAVEAT: honesty at the API level does not guarantee that Cortex will
actually be populated with user history at inference. That is a runtime-
wiring concern for the copilot/rag layer, not a corpus concern.
"

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; TOP FINDINGS
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  :top-10-findings-by-severity
"# Top 10 findings ranked by severity

## SEVERITY 1 (ship-blocking for 1.0; acceptable for 0.75 exploration)

1. MODULES-NOT-EXTENSIONS TERMINOLOGY VIOLATION (390 rows).
   Doctrine (project_modules_not_extensions_2026_07_17) says: 'In Motoi
   they're MODULES, not extensions ... Never say extensions.' Corpus
   ships 390 rows containing 'book-of-extensions' (source file still
   named wave-1-book-of-extensions-2026-07-16.jsonl) and 165 rows using
   'extension(s)' in prose. Model will learn 'extension' as the default
   word. Fix: rename source file, regex-rewrite in-place, refold.

2. BOOK-OF-MODULES IS EMPTY.
   scheme-books/book-of-modules/ contains zero chapter files. The doctrine
   requires 16 chapters + appendices. If a user runs (book/read :book
   'modules), reader returns nothing. Motoi will confidently talk about
   modules but have no book to point at. Fix: promote wave-1-book-of-
   extensions content into scheme-books/book-of-modules with renamed
   terminology.

3. SAKURA-DIALECT LEAKAGE INTO MOTOI CORPUS (559 rows).
   sakura-scheme-lang fenced blocks, radio/* verbs, chime-shop-closing
   examples, and 'the Sakura reference exposes ...' prose appear inside
   Motoi training-data. Doctrine (variant-vs-fork; Motoi = base) requires
   these to live in the consumer dialect repo, not in Motoi. The persona-
   firewall claim of 413-removed did not catch these. Fix: widen firewall
   patterns to include sakura-scheme fence markers, radio/*, chime-*,
   card/*, shop/*, cine/*, etc.

## SEVERITY 2 (fix before 1.0; monitor at 0.75)

4. AUTHORING-INSTRUCTION LEAKS IN USER TURNS (8 rows).
   'A cuff sold as antique Georg Jensen (do not brand-name in operator
   listing without verification) ...' — parenthetical author notes got
   serialized into user turns. Fix: regex '\\(do not [^)]+\\)' → strip;
   refold.

5. ANTIQUE-JEWELRY VOCAB DRIFT FROM 11-YEAR-OLD FRAME (~145 rows).
   Georg Jensen, Cartier, 830 silver, Continental European, hollow gold
   band — adult vocabulary that shouldn't be in a kid's assistant.
   Concentrated in graph-vocab-pairs + marcus-2-word-books. Fix: firewall
   filter for antique/luxury-brand tokens; refold.

6. AUDIO CORE VERBS UNDEFINED IN RUNTIME (7).
   audio/bar-clock, audio/key, audio/listen, audio/lufs, audio/onset-strength,
   audio/onset?, audio/spectrum documented as CORE and FROZEN but not
   defined in runtime. Model will emit; runtime will throw. Fix: either
   implement (DSP work) or reclassify to MODULE (doctrine amendment).

7. PATH-GUARD ADOPTION IS PARTIAL.
   Only 2 of 9 file-touching modules use lib/security/path-guard.safePath.
   Others rely on constant paths or bespoke guards. Priya's Wave-1 P-01
   fix in http-serve is bespoke and sturdy, but there is no repo-wide
   discipline. Fix: adopt safePath everywhere; add lint rule.

## SEVERITY 3 (nice-to-fix; not urgent)

8. BOOK CHAPTER INVARIANT VIOLATIONS.
   5 books below 16 chapters (challenges/logic/modules/systems +
   modules-is-empty); book-of-motion has 23 (overflow); 6 books missing
   MANIFEST. Fix: extend thin ones, overflow motion → appendices, author
   missing MANIFESTs.

9. AUDIO-DRIVER SHELL-OUT NOT DOCUMENTED AS EXCEPTION.
   lib/audio/audio-driver.js imports spawn from node:child_process.
   Doctrine motoi-no-tools-no-internet says no shell-out. If this is
   fixed-binary /usr/bin/afplay + fixed-flags it may be acceptable but
   must be documented in SECURITY-CANONICAL. Currently silent.

10. SAFETY-CRITICAL ROWS ARE THIN (40 of 89,246 = 0.045%).
    Correct template, but tiny volume. Model may under-weight. Fix:
    upsample safety-critical rows 5x-10x for the LoRA-on-finer pass.
"

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; FIX LIST BY LEVERAGE
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  :fix-list-by-leverage
"# Fix list ordered by leverage (highest-impact-per-effort first)

## 1. Refold with terminology firewall + jewelry firewall (leverage: 10)

Effort: ~1 hour. Impact: closes findings #1, #3, #4, #5 simultaneously.

Add to fold script the following pattern strips over each pair (both user
and assistant turns):

  - regex 'book-of-extensions' → 'book-of-modules'
  - regex '\\bextension(s)?\\b' (word-boundary) → 'module\\1' in prose only,
    NOT inside code fences (protect '(import extension ...)' syntax if any)
  - regex '\\(do not [^)]+\\)' → strip (removes 8 authoring-leak rows)
  - firewall additions: sakura-scheme fence marker, radio/*, chime-*,
    card/*, shop/*, cine/*, flower/*, marionette/*, cadence/*, need/*,
    afford/*, ai-sidecar/*
  - luxury/antique tokens: georg-jensen, cartier, tiffany, sterling-silver,
    830-silver, continental-european-silver, hollow-gold-band, antique-jewelry
    (strip pair OR downweight; recommend strip)

Rename source file: git mv wave-1-book-of-extensions-2026-07-16.jsonl →
wave-1-book-of-modules-2026-07-16.jsonl (and update manifest source-list).

## 2. Populate book-of-modules (leverage: 8)

Effort: ~2 hours. Impact: closes finding #2; makes book-reader honest
about the modules terminology.

Take existing book-of-extensions material (was consolidated into training-
data wave-1 file) and structure it as 16 chapters in
scheme-books/book-of-modules/. Add MANIFEST.book.slatl. Ship terminology-
correct.

## 3. Reclassify or implement 7 audio CORE verbs (leverage: 6)

Effort: 30 min (reclassify) OR ~1 week (implement DSP). Impact: closes
finding #6.

Recommend: DECLASSIFY from CORE for 0.75 (edit core/core-verbs.js,
document in reference as MODULE with 'planned DSP work' note). Motoi 1.0
can promote back to CORE after implementation.

## 4. Upsample safety-critical rows (leverage: 5)

Effort: 15 min (fold script tweak). Impact: closes finding #10;
strengthens finding-1 safety consistency at model level.

Duplicate the 40 safety-critical rows 5-10x during the LoRA-on-finer
stage (SFT stage should NOT duplicate — bias risk). Alternative: create
a small 'safety-reinforcement' JSONL that runs post-SFT.

## 5. Adopt safePath everywhere + document audio-driver exception (leverage: 4)

Effort: ~3 hours. Impact: closes findings #7, #9.

Add safePath to media.js, artifact.js, cortex-io.js, book/reader.js.
Add lint rule 'no-fs-outside-safepath'. Document audio-driver.js shell-out
in SECURITY-CANONICAL as fixed-binary exception with allowlist.

## 6. Book invariant sweep (leverage: 3)

Effort: ~4 hours (largely mechanical). Impact: closes finding #8.

Extend under-16 books (challenges/logic/systems) with 1-2 chapters each.
Split book-of-motion 23-chapter into 16 chapters + 7 appendices. Author
missing MANIFEST.book.slatl files for 6 books.
"

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; SHIP/FIX DECISIONS FOR ALFRED
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  :alfred-decisions
"# Ship-vs-fix decisions for Alfred (in priority order)

## DECISION 1: Terminology violation — ship or refold?

The 'modules not extensions' lock is DURABLE per Alfred (2026-07-17).
390 rows in train.jsonl teach 'book-of-extensions'. If the 0.75 run
completes as-is, Motoi will say 'extensions' when Alfred said 'modules'.

Options:
  (a) STOP run-2, refold with terminology firewall, restart.
  (b) LET run-2 complete for exploration; do not ship 0.75; refold + retrain for real 0.75.
  (c) LET run-2 complete; accept as 0.75 with a documented
      terminology-drift caveat; fix in 1.0.

Auditor recommendation: (b). The exploration run is not wasted — Alfred
gets to see the persona voice and safety behavior. But shipping 0.75
with the terminology violation would harden the wrong word into the
model's identity.

## DECISION 2: Sakura-dialect leakage — how strict?

559 rows mention 'sakura'. Many are legitimate meta-references ('Sakura
is a persona. I am a copilot. We share ancestry.'). Some are dialect
leakage ('```sakura-scheme' fence + radio/* + chime-shop-closing).

Options:
  (a) Filter ALL 'sakura' mentions — loses legitimate ancestry pairs.
  (b) Filter only DIALECT LEAKAGE (fenced sakura-scheme blocks + dialect
      verbs), keep prose ancestry references.
  (c) Ship as-is; accept as 'Motoi knows Sakura exists.'

Auditor recommendation: (b). Author a smarter firewall.

## DECISION 3: Book-of-modules — populate now or 1.0?

The book is empty. Model will train knowing the word 'modules' (once fix
1 lands) but the runtime book-reader will return nothing.

Options:
  (a) POPULATE now: 2-hour effort by any authoring lane.
  (b) STUB now: a single 'coming soon' chapter so book/read returns
      something honest.
  (c) DEFER to 1.0: accept that book/read on modules is empty.

Auditor recommendation: (b) STUB now to satisfy the invariant honestly,
(a) POPULATE before 1.0.

## DECISION 4: Antique-jewelry vocab — strip or shrug?

145 rows use adult antique/luxury vocabulary that drifts from the 11-year-
old frame. It came from graph-vocab-pairs (auto-generated from platform
category vocab).

Options:
  (a) STRIP all luxury-tokens; refold.
  (b) DOWNWEIGHT during training (assign lower loss weight).
  (c) SHIP: 145 of 89,246 is 0.16%; noise-level.

Auditor recommendation: (a) STRIP. Percentage is small, but the content
is JARRING when sampled and violates the 11-year-old frame Alfred
authored. Zero cost to strip; nonzero cost to keep.

## DECISION 5: Run-2 disposition

If Alfred wants to preserve the training compute already spent:
  - COMPLETE run-2 for exploration/observation
  - DO NOT accept as shippable 0.75
  - After a follow-up fold (fold-v3) with fixes above, run a fresh 0.75

If Alfred wants to correct the terminology BEFORE further training compute:
  - STOP run-2 at next safe checkpoint
  - Fix (leverages 1+2 above) — ~3 hours of authoring
  - Refold as fold-v3
  - Restart
"

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; VERDICT
  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  :verdict "NEEDS-FIX"
  :verdict-summary
"Motoi 0.75 corpus is SAFE, HONEST, and CONSISTENT on the ship-blocking
dimensions: safety refusals (100%), tool-strip (100%), Cortex-integration
honesty (100%), and persona doctrine coverage (11/11 waves).

Corpus is NOT-YET-READY on: modules-vs-extensions terminology (390 rows
teach the wrong word), Sakura-dialect leakage (559 rows), 11-year-old
frame drift (145 antique-jewelry rows), book-of-modules empty, and 8
CORE verbs undefined in runtime.

None of the failures are unrecoverable. Alfred can either (a) let run-2
complete as exploration and refold-then-retrain for real 0.75, or (b)
stop run-2 and fix now. The auditor recommends option (a) — run-2 will
still teach us the persona voice + safety behavior, which are the
hardest things to get right, and both are correctly implemented.

Ship-blocking gap for a real 0.75 release: modules-not-extensions
terminology + Sakura-dialect leakage. Both fixable in ~3 hours of
authoring + one fold cycle.
"

  ; ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ; AUDIT GAPS (things this audit did NOT cover)
