  :audit-gaps
"# Sections not fully covered — logged as audit-gaps

1. Did not evaluate the model itself (run-2 still in progress; no
   generated outputs to score). Every finding here is on CORPUS + RUNTIME,
   not on TRAINED MODEL BEHAVIOR.

2. Did not do a per-verb count of reference documentation vs runtime
   for the full 962 documented verbs. Only verified the 335 CORE set.

3. Did not exhaustively verify that every persona pair claim about
   verb behavior matches runtime semantics — only cross-checked Cortex
   family (5 pairs, 100% backed).

4. Did not exercise the 55 wave-8 circular-trap prompts against the
   TRAINED model. Wave 8's efficacy is a post-training empirical question.

5. Book-of-modules count is FILE-COUNT ONLY. Did not verify chapter
   quality inside populated books (16 files doesn't mean 16 quality
   chapters).

6. Persona-firewall claim of 413-removed was not audited row-by-row.
   Trusted the fold-report count; verified only that the outcome retains
   detectable Sakura-dialect content (559 rows).

7. Did not run static analysis on lib/ for other doctrine violations
   beyond fs/child_process. e.g. did not check for network fetch()
   surfaces or WebSocket clients.
"

